Articles.Content:
What mods do you have?

Unless specified, you shouldn't expect 1.2 mods to work with 1.3.

Don't stick the log in the forum, it messes things up. And that's not the right log anyways. 

Upload your output log to a website like dropbox and paste the link here.

Like Gaarst said, you shouldn't expect mods for 1.2 or before to work for 1.3. likewise you shouldn't expect mods for 1.3 to work for 1.2.

Also, if you have the steam version, it is recommended that you make a second copy of the game to mod.

As usual at least 95% of all mod related issues are caused by (in order of likelihood):

  1. Incompatible or outdated mods.
  2. Incorrect installation
  3. Missing or conflicting dependencies.

In other words:

  1. Only install mods that are compatible with your current KSP version. Old (not updated) mods might not work on the latest KSP while updated mods might not work on older KSP versions.
  2. Closely follow the installation instructions!
  3. If a mod description states it is dependant on an other mod accept that statement as a fact. You WILL need it.

You need to update all your old mods.

However, you may have a stray file that is causing a problem. (i.e. cruft/lint)

I recommend purging all your old mod versions and reinstalling them in case a piece of cruft is causing a problem.  (Searching for cruft falls under the kind of work that even the most obsessive computer engineer does not enjoy.  Often the easier solution is to note what should be there.  Delete it all, and re-install it from the cleanest source available.  In this case the various mod repositories or CKAN's repository, depending if the mod is compatible with CKAN.)

If a mod contains a .dll module that is compiled for 1.2.x or earlier you may run into serious issues if the dll is not updated.   For all mods that contain dlls get the latest version of the dll, usually available from a link on the mod's page or by searching for the dll.  (e.g. googling "Firespitter KSP 1.3" or "Module Manager KSP 1.3")
